  <fr:p>Let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\chi _x \colon  a = x]]></fr:tex> be the witness of contraction for any <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[x:A]]></fr:tex>. Given <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[b : Ba]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[x:A]]></fr:tex>, we define <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathsf {ind}_{A,a}\,b\,x : Bx]]></fr:tex> by transporting <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[b]]></fr:tex> along the identification <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\chi _a^{-1} \cdot  \chi _x \colon  a = x]]></fr:tex>:</fr:p>

  <fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[     \mathsf {ind}_{A,a}\,b\,x :\equiv        \mathopen {}\left \lparen \chi _a^{-1}\cdot \chi _x\right \rparen \mathclose {} _* b   ]]></fr:tex>

  <fr:p>Then we compute <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathsf {ind}_{A,a}\,b\,a \equiv    \mathopen {}\left \lparen \chi _a^{-1}\cdot \chi _a\right \rparen \mathclose {} _* b  = \mathsf {refl}_*b = b]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
