display="inline"><![CDATA[a]]></fr:tex>. For any family of types <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[B\colon  A \to  \mathsf {Type}]]></fr:tex>, we may define a function <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathsf {ind}_{A,a}\colon  B a \to  \mathchoice {\textstyle \prod _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x : A\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}{\textstyle \prod _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x : A\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}{\scriptstyle \prod _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x : A\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}{\scriptscriptstyle \prod _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x : A\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}Bx]]></fr:tex> satisfying <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathsf {ind}_{A,a}\,b\,a = b]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
 
   
